e 19), providing import.meta.url and import.meta.resolve() functionality. Module caching is handled by lib/internal/modules/esm/module_map.js with ResolveCache (line 25) and LoadCache (line 89) classes maintaining module registration states.\n\nSupporting components include lib/internal/modules/esm/utils.js which exports compileSourceTextModule() (line 336) for translating source into modules and initializeESM() (line 276) for ESM initialization. Loader hooks are implemented through the Hooks class (lib/internal/modules/esm/hooks.js, line 108) and HooksProxy (line 472) enabling customization of the resolve and load hooks. Format utilities in lib/internal/modules/esm/formats.js provide mimeToFormat() (line 36) and getFormatOfExtensionlessFile() (line 54). Dynamic module creation is supported through lib/internal/modules/esm/create_dynamic_module.js. Helper utilities in lib/internal/modules/helpers.js including urlToFilename() (line 282) and normalizeReferrerURL() (line 257) support URL-to-path conversions and module reference normalization."
